<br>
It was cold, well the air wasn’t, but the concrete floor of the parking garage on which I was laying when I woke was in the extreme. You have to ask yourself several important questions when you find you are lying on your face in a pool of your own sweat in a rundown cheap parking complex. Chief among these questions would be of course, where the hell am I, which leads to the second question, how did I get here and inevitably leads to the third and final question, why am I lying face first on a cold concrete slab of a floor? As I pondered these important questions my head began to swim, it appeared that I had a forth question, why did my head hurt so much? It occurred to me that perhaps I should stand up and assess the situation. At first my right leg had decided to be a bit stubborn but after a bit of coaxing and a promise of a hot bath and a soft mattress it decided it would cooperate. As soon as I reached full extension, my leg decided that now was the appropriate time to inform me that there was a bullet that had somehow found its was into the area just below my knee. Upon receiving this trivial bit of information my mind decided that it agreed with my leg and then informed it to collapse on the spot. So here I was once again lying on the concrete, my leg and head throbbing and my mind attempting to cope with the current situation. Suddenly I became aware of everything around me. It appeared that while seedy, rundown and extremely cold the garage was not empty, it contained a Volkswagen Beetle, a Honda Accord, a Toyota pickup and a bullet ridden beat up jalopy that slightly resembled a Honda Civic. I stuck my hand in the pocket of my soiled bloodied suit pants and produce a set of keys, a business card, a Zippo lighter, and a crushed pack of Marblo cigarettes. I decided that if at any time in my life I was going to destroy my body by slowly killing it with tar, now would be the time.  I lit the cigarette and inhaled. Once again I looked around, and took into account my surroundings and informed my leg that I wasn’t putting up with its mutiny any longer and it was time to get down to the business it was created for. So slowly I stood up. I gritted my teeth, took a deep breath and propped my self up on the nearest car, which was the Toyota pickup. I took another drag of the cigarette, and decided that perhaps it was time to find out which car if any the set of keys in my pocket belonged to. Common sense dictated that they belonged to the truck I was leaning on, so I slowly moved to the door, inserted the keys and was rewarded for my hard work with absolutely nothing. It appeared that common sense did not apply to this situation. I looked around to the next closest car, it was the beetle. I shuffled over and inserted the key, once again nothing happed, it was at this point I started to become a little uneasy, the thought had slipped into my mind that only 2 cars remained. So slowly I made my way over to the Accord, and after unsuccessfully attempting several times to force the key to work, I released a string of curses that would have dropped a catholic priest from 300 yards. So now obviously the only car remaining was the civic look alike. I hobbled over and inserted the key. Bullet holes riddled the door, there was a broken back window, and a missing side view mirror. Holding my breath I turned the key hoping that they belonged to none of the cars in the lot. It appeared I was @#%$ out of luck. I opened the door. Inside the drivers seat was covered in blood, there was a destroyed Styrofoam coffee cup, and a silver colt .45 in between the seats. I sat down, cursing my luck. I took another drag of my cigarette and started the engine. It choked at first but finally, obviously against its will rumbled to a start. I pulled out of the spot and decided I’d stop by the hospital. If worse came too worse at least I could steal some painkillers. I took another drag, flicked the butt out the window and putted off.  <br>
