<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp When the world came back into focus the sun had come up and I was staring strait down the wrong end of a large revolver. “Get up Jackson, its 10:30” the voice had come from the knock out blonde from the file. If it weren’t for the gun I would have had to say that she looked better in person. “@#%$ it Jackson get up!” I sat up as she put the gun away. “What the hell happened, you were supposed to be at the club last night.” <br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp “What? I’m not jackso…” The dejavu from the night before and the picture came back. I was Jackson Socrates the slobish private eye with the dime novel office. No wonder I like his style so much. “What happened?”<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp “How should I know, you were the one who didn’t show up, and what happened to your leg?” the pain suddenly shot back like a bad memory. <br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp “Well, it appears I’ve been shot, now if you don’t mind could you reach into my coat pocket and get me that bottle of pain killer, it hurts quite a bit.” She walked over to the coat and threw me the bottle. I popped a few less than the night before remembering the kid with the hat, and pulled myself into a standing position. Letting out a long sigh I ran my hand through my hair, I need a shower not to mention a change of clothes. <br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp “Lets go Jackson its not safe here,” she looked very adamant about the fact that this was an unsafe place. With the gun away and the painkillers starting to take affect I was almost speechless staring at her. I saved face by managing to stammer ok, let me just see if I have any other clothes around here. I hobbled over to the closet and found a black suit and a red tie. <br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp “Hold on a sec,” I said walking into the bathroom. I changed into the new suit and ran some water over my face, and then looked into the mirror. Once again I had to question my state of mind as I found a man in his early 30’s staring me back in the face. I was strait out of a dime novel myself, black hair, weathered face and a five o’clock shadow that looked like someone had inked it on. I opened the bathroom door and was greeted by the lovely angelica sitting on my desk. She had nice legs, very nice legs. <br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp “Ok, finally done. You look better now, not so dead looking, did you find anything else out about my fathers plans?” she asked. <br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp “No” I said. Kneeling in front of the safe I took out the cash and the clips figuring they belonged to the gun in the car out side. Never know, I might need em if the guy in the brown suit ever got out of the slammer. We walked out the door to the car and got in. “Well, the truth is Angelica.”<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp “Please I already told you call me Angel” she said with a smile that would give a old man a heat attack. <br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp “OK Angel, the truth is that I don’t remember much before last night, it’s kind of a blur.” No sooner had I finished my sentence than a large black Cadillac pulled up across the street. The door opened and the figure of a large man in a brown suit accented to full height. “Oh @#%$.” I push Angel out of the car and dove after her just as what was left of my car was ripped to shreds in a hail of gunfire. Glass flew through the air and the sound of metal folding under extreme pressure filled my ears. Suddenly Angel stood up and fired 3 shoots from her large revolver. The Cadillac’s passenger window exploded and the other two shots implanted them selves into the door. She grabbed my arm and pulled me back into the office just as I saw my cheap sign shatter. We crawled on our knees to behind the desk.<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp “Ok Jackson now would be the time to use that piece you got there” and with that she stood up and fired through the window at the advancing thug. I noticed before he ducked behind the ruble that was my car that he had a bandage on his head, I got a little satisfaction out of that. For about a minute the area around my office was like the scene of a gang war, bullets flying all over the place, wood chips flying glass shattering, paper being thrown all over the place. “Quick out the back” yelled Angel over the crack of multiple shot. I got up and fired a few shots and then we ran top speed out the back door and into the alley. “Hurry, I parked my car over there.” We sprinted to her bright red Mazda Miata, it seemed to fit her well. It had a black leather interior and smelled of fruity perfume. As soon as I shut the door we were off flying down the street as fast as the car could. We ripped around the corner at about 75 miles per hour and I saw that brown suit thug spin around and raise his gun. But we were already down the street and around another corner. “That was close, I told you it wasn’t safe in there.” It appeared she was right, and she did look better in person.<br>
